y.nasa.gov/monograph18.pdf X-15 flight history (altitudes given in feet)]\n*[https://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/planetary/gemini.html Gemini flight history]\n*[https://www.nasa.gov/audience/forstudents/5-8/features/nasa-knows/what-was-apollo-program-58.html Apollo flight history (student resource)]\n*[https://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/skylab/missions/skylab_manned.html Skylab flight history]\n*[https://www.nasa.gov/apollo-soyuz/overview Apollo-Soyuz flight history]\n*[https://www.nasa.gov/pdf/537939main_ss-launches-080311.pdf Space Shuttle flight history infographic]\n*[http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2013-06/12/content_16609614.htm Shenzhou flight history timeline]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100822194232/http://www.scaled.com/projects/tierone/combined_white_knight_spaceshipone_flight_tests SpaceShipOne flight history]\n*[http://russianspaceweb.com/soyuz-ms-10.html Soyuz MS-10 flight details]\n*[https://edition.cnn.com/2018/12/13/tech/virgin-galactic-reaches-50-mile-space/index.html VSS ''Unity'' flight details]\n*[https://www.iflscience.com/space/virgin-galactic-space-plane-just-took-its-first-test-passenger-to-space/]\n\n{{Space exploration lists and timelines}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List of human spaceflights, 2011-2020}}\n[[Category:Human spaceflight]]\n[[Category:Lists of astronauts|2010]]\n[[Category:Spaceflight timelines]]\n[[Category:21st century-related lists|Human spaceflights, 2011-present]]\n[[Category:2010s-related lists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a detailed '''list of human spaceflights from 2011 to the present'''.\n\n*<span style=\"background: #BBFFBB;\">Green</span> indicates a [[Sub-orbital spaceflight#Manned sub-orbital spaceflights|suborbital flight]] (including flights that failed to attain intended orbit).\n{| class=\"wikitable\" rules=all cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"3\" align=center style=\"border: 1px solid #555555; text-align: center\"\n|-\n! #\n! width=\"23%\"|Crew\n! Launch<br>spacecraft\n! co